16/11/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia and the EU signed a memorandum of understanding Monday (15 November) on the EU pre-accession technical assistance programme Matra for 2005.
It envisions co-operation between Croatian and EU institutions in conducting administrative reforms in various sectors, in order to strengthen Croatian institutions ahead of EU membership.
In other news Monday, the president of the UN war crimes tribunal, Theodor Meron, told the UN General Assembly that Croatia has markedly improved co-operation with the tribunal.
He was assessing relations between the tribunal and various countries.
(Vecernji list - 16/11/04;
HINA, HRT, Tanjug - 15/11/04)
